-- Afghanistan's Helmand Province Has Deposits of Rare Earths, Official Says
-- B y   G o p a l   R a t n a m
-- 2010-10-26T15:34:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/afghanistan-s-helmand-province-has-deposits-of-rare-earths-official-says.html
Afghanistan’s Helmand province,
where the U.S. military is fighting the Taliban, has deposits of
rare-earth elements including lanthanum and cerium, Atiq Sediqi,
an adviser to Afghanistan’s Ministry of Mines, said in an
interview in Washington.  Sediqi spoke during the Critical & Rare Metals Summit III
conference in today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gopal Ratnam in Washington at 
 gratnam1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Liebert at 
 lliebert@bloomberg.net  